# Implementation Plan - Feature AC: Learning Transfer Challenges (Version 2)

This plan details the technical steps to implement **Learning Transfer Challenges (Feature AC)** in the Tenali platform. **Version 2** extends this feature dynamically to **all** learning modules using a dynamic wrapper system, enabling real-world context challenges for any possible topic key.

---

## Proposed Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Topic Welcome Box] -->|Stage 3 Completed?| B(Show 'Start Transfer Challenge' CTA)
    B -->|Click| C[Transfer Challenge Interface]
    C -->|Fetch Q| D[GET /transfer-api/question]
    D -->|Serves stateless template & vars| C
    C -->|Submit Answer| E[POST /transfer-api/check]
    E -->|Deterministic Validation| F{Correct?}
    F -->|No| G[Show Diagnostic Feedback & Transfer Mapping]
    F -->|Yes| H[Increment Transfer Progress]
    H -->|2 Correct?| I[Award Gold Mastery + 75 Sun Coins]
```

To preserve Tenali's core principles, this feature implements **Approach C (Hybrid Curated Templates with Parametric Expansion)**. Scenarios are generated deterministically from pre-authored templates by plugging in randomized variables. The client stays lightweight, and answer checking runs statelessly on the server.

